        <div n="Y48A33HK" type="poem"><head type="note" n="1" xml:id="spp-Y48A33HK-headnote-1"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-Y48A33HK-headnote-1-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-Y48A33HK-headnote-1-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head><head type="note" n="2" xml:id="spp-Y48A33HK-headnote-2"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-Y48A33HK-headnote-2-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-Y48A33HK-headnote-2-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head><head type="note" n="3" xml:id="spp-Y48A33HK-headnote-3"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-Y48A33HK-headnote-3-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-Y48A33HK-headnote-3-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head>
      <lg n="1" type="stanza"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-Y48A33HK-line-1"><hi rend="display-initial">T</hi>HE Furniture that best doth please</l><l n="2" xml:id="spp-Y48A33HK-line-2"> St. Patrick's Dean, good Sir, are these;</l><l n="3" xml:id="spp-Y48A33HK-line-3"> The Knife and Fork, with which I eat,</l><l n="4" xml:id="spp-Y48A33HK-line-4"> And next the Pot that boils the Meat;</l><l n="5" xml:id="spp-Y48A33HK-line-5"> The next to be preferr'd, I think,</l><l n="6" xml:id="spp-Y48A33HK-line-6"> Is the Glass in which I drink;</l><l n="7" xml:id="spp-Y48A33HK-line-7"> The Shelves on which my Books I keep,</l><l n="8" xml:id="spp-Y48A33HK-line-8"> And the Bed in which I Sleep;</l><l n="9" xml:id="spp-Y48A33HK-line-9"> An Antique Elbow Chair between,</l><l n="10" xml:id="spp-Y48A33HK-line-10"> Big enough to hold the Dean;</l><l n="11" xml:id="spp-Y48A33HK-line-11"> And the Stove that gives Delight,</l><l n="12" xml:id="spp-Y48A33HK-line-12"> In the cold bleak wintry Night;</l><l n="13" xml:id="spp-Y48A33HK-line-13"> To these we add a Thing below,</l><l n="14" xml:id="spp-Y48A33HK-line-14"> More for Use reserv'd than Shew:</l><l n="15" xml:id="spp-Y48A33HK-line-15"> These are what the Dean do please,</l><l n="16" xml:id="spp-Y48A33HK-line-16"> All superfluous are but these.Y48A33HK   </l></lg></div>
      </div>
